[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.core.config.LoggerConfig.log[0m[1m([0mLoggerConfig.jav[1;92ma:407[0m[1m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.core.config.LoggerConfig.log[0m[1m([0mLoggerConfig.jav[1;92ma:368[0m[1m)[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at [1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.core.Logger.log[0m[1m([0mLogger.jav[1;92ma:110[0m[1m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.spi.AbstractLogger.warn[0m[1m([0mAbstractLogger.jav[1;92ma:1916[0m[1m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                 at                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mSimpleLoggerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:42[0m[1m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: 03a39a742f79fa3d                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Jazzer-guided fuzzing run has identified a critical security issue in the Apache  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Log4j lookup mechanism: a remote JNDI lookup can be performed using an              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         attacker-controlled URL. This behavior is flagged as `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical`  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         because it may lead to remote code execution or sensitive data exfiltration,        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         depending on the JDK version in use.                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Issue Overview                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           During fuzz testing, the fuzzer invoked a JNDI lookup with a remote URL that can  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         be controlled by an attacker. The lookup was processed through the Log4j            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookup` class, resulting in a critical security finding.                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Vulnerability Type                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           The issue is classified as a **Remote JNDI Lookup** vulnerability. Unvalidated    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         JNDI lookups with external URLs are known to potentially provide an attacker with   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         remote code execution capabilities or allow malicious retrieval of internal data.   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Key Observations                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The Jazzer sanitizer hook [1m([0m`NamingContextLookup.lookupHook`[1m)[0m detected the       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         remote lookup and threw `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical`.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The stack trace shows the lookup originating in                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup.lookup[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • Subsequent calls in the trace go through Log4j’s `Interpolator`,                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `StrSubstitutor`, `MessagePatternConverter`, and `PatternLayout` layers—indicating  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         the lookup is performed as part of normal log message formatting.                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           • The fuzzer entry point is `SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`, but this     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         serves only to trigger the lookup logic and is not the root cause.                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - Code Areas for Investigation                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           To understand the full impact and remediation scope, the following components     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         should be reviewed:                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m1[0m. **org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup** – how it constructs and    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         executes JNDI calls.                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m2[0m. **NamingContextLookup [1m([0mJazzer sanitizer hook[1m)[0m** – the detection mechanism and  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         any configuration allowing external lookups.                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m3[0m. **Interpolator & StrSubstitutor** – how variable resolution leads to JNDI      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         lookups in formatted messages.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m4[0m. **PatternLayout and related formatting classes** – determine if other lookup   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         types or patterns could trigger the same behavior.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m           [1;36m5[0m. **Logging configuration and user-controlled inputs** – assess how log messages [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         are built and where untrusted data might be injected.                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m<[0m[1;95missue[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== Java Exception: com.code_intelligence.jazzer.api.FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mRemote JNDI Lookup[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJNDI lookups with attacker-controlled remote URLs can, depending on the JDK[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mversion, lead to remote code execution or the exfiltration of information.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m17[0m[39m:package org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m18[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m19[0m[39m:import java.util.ArrayList;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m20[0m[39m:import java.util.Enumeration;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m21[0m[39m:import java.util.HashMap;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m22[0m[39m:import java.util.Iterator;[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m23[0m[39m:import java.util.List;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m24[0m[39m:import java.util.Map;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m25[0m[39m:import java.util.Properties;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m26[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m27[0m[39m:import org.apache.logging.log4j.core.LogEvent;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m28[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m29[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m: * Substitutes variables within a string by values.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m: * This class takes a piece of text and substitutes all the variables within it.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m: * The default definition of a variable is <code>$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mvariableName[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>.[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m: * The prefix and suffix can be changed via constructors and set methods.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m: * Variable values are typically resolved from a map, but could also be resolved[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m: * from system properties, or by supplying a custom variable resolver.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m39[0m[39m: * The simplest example is to use this class to replace Java System properties. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mFor example:[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m40[0m[39m: * <pre>[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m41[0m[39m: * [0m[1;35mStrSubstitutor.replaceSystemProperties[0m[1;39m([0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m42[0m[39m: *      [0m[32m"You are running with java.version = $[0m[32m{[0m[32mjava.version[0m[32m}[0m[32m and os.name = [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m$[0m[32m{[0m[32mos.name[0m[32m}[0m[32m."[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m43[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mpre[0m[39m>[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m44[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m: * Typical usage of this class follows the following pattern: First an instance [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis created[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m46[0m[39m: * and initialized with the map that contains the values for the available [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariables.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m47[0m[39m: * If a prefix and/or suffix for variables should be used other than the default[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mones,[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m: * the appropriate settings can be performed. After that the [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m[1;35mreplace[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m49[0m[39m: * method can be called passing in the source text for interpolation. In the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreturned[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m: * text all variable references [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas long as their values are known[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m will be [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresolved.[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m51[0m[39m: * The following example demonstrates this:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m52[0m[39m: * <pre>[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m: * Map valuesMap = [0m[1;35mHashMap[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m54[0m[39m: * [0m[1;35mvaluesMap.put[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&quot;animal&quot;, &quot;quick brown fox&quot;[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m: * [0m[1;35mvaluesMap.put[0m[1;39m([0m[39m&quot;target&quot;, &quot;lazy dog&quot;[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m: * String templateString = &quot;The $[0m[1;39m{[0m[39manimal[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m jumped over the $[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mtarget[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m.&quot;;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m57[0m[39m: * StrSubstitutor sub = new [0m[1;35mStrSubstitutor[0m[1;39m([0m[39mvaluesMap[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m58[0m[39m: * String resolvedString = [0m[1;35msub.replace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtemplateString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m59[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mpre[0m[39m>[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m60[0m[39m: * yielding:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m61[0m[39m: * <pre>[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m: *      The quick brown fox jumped over the lazy dog.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mpre[0m[39m>[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m: * In addition to this usage pattern there are some static convenience methods [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m: * cover the most common use cases. These methods can be used without the need [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m: * manually creating an instance. However if multiple replace operations are to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m: * performed, creating and reusing an instance of this class will be more [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mefficient.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m69[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m: * Variable replacement works in a recursive way. Thus, if a variable value [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontains[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m: * a variable then that variable will also be replaced. Cyclic replacements are[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m: * detected and will cause an exception to be thrown.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m: * Sometimes the interpolation's result must contain a variable prefix. As an [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexample[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m75[0m[39m: * take the following source text:[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m76[0m[39m: * <pre>[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m77[0m[39m: *   The variable $[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mname[0m[1;39m}[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m must be used.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m78[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mpre[0m[39m>[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m79[0m[39m: * Here only the variable's name referred to in the text should be replaced [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresulting[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m80[0m[39m: * in the text [0m[1;39m([0m[39massuming that the value of the <code>name<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m> variable is [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>x<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m81[0m[39m: * <pre>[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m82[0m[39m: *   The variable $[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mx[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m must be used.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m83[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mpre[0m[39m>[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m84[0m[39m: * To achieve this effect there are two possibilities: Either set a different [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprefix[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m85[0m[39m: * and suffix for variables which do not conflict with the result text you want [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m86[0m[39m: * produce. The other possibility is to use the escape character, by default [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m'$'[0m[39m.[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m87[0m[39m: * If this character is placed before a variable reference, this reference is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mignored[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m88[0m[39m: * and won't be replaced. For example:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m89[0m[39m: * <pre>[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m90[0m[39m: *   The variable $$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mname[0m[1;39m}[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m must be used.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m91[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mpre[0m[39m>[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m92[0m[39m: * <p>[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m93[0m[39m: * In some complex scenarios you might even want to perform substitution in the[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m94[0m[39m: * names of variables, for instance[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m95[0m[39m: * <pre>[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m96[0m[39m: * $[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mjre-$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mjava.specification.version[0m[1;39m}[0m[1;39m}[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m97[0m[39m: * <[0m[35m/[0m[95mpre[0m[39m>[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m98[0m[39m: * <code>StrSubstitutor<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m> supports this recursive substitution in variable[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m99[0m[39m: * names, but it has to be enabled explicitly by setting the[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m100[0m[39m: * [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m@link #[0m[1;35msetEnableSubstitutionInVariables[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menableSubstitutionInVariables[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m101[0m[39m: * property to <b>true<[0m[35m/[0m[95mb[0m[39m>.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m102[0m[39m: *[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m103[0m[39m: *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m104[0m[39m:public class StrSubstitutor [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m105[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m106[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m107[0m[39m:     * Constant for the default escape character.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m108[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m109[0m[39m:    public static final char DEFAULT_ESCAPE = [0m[32m'$'[0m[39m;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m110[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m111[0m[39m:     * Constant for the default variable prefix.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m112[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m113[0m[39m:    public static final StrMatcher DEFAULT_PREFIX = [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mStrMatcher.stringMatcher[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"$[0m[32m{[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m114[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m115[0m[39m:     * Constant for the default variable suffix.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m116[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m117[0m[39m:    public static final StrMatcher DEFAULT_SUFFIX = [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mStrMatcher.stringMatcher[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m118[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m119[0m[39m:    private static final int BUF_SIZE = [0m[1;36m256[0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m120[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m121[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m122[0m[39m:     * Stores the escape character.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m123[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m124[0m[39m:    private char escapeChar;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m125[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m126[0m[39m:     * Stores the variable prefix.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m127[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m128[0m[39m:    private StrMatcher prefixMatcher;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m129[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m[39m:     * Stores the variable suffix.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m131[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m132[0m[39m:    private StrMatcher suffixMatcher;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m133[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m134[0m[39m:     * Variable resolution is delegated to an implementer of VariableResolver.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m135[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m136[0m[39m:    private StrLookup variableResolver;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m137[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m138[0m[39m:     * The flag whether substitution in variable names is enabled.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m139[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m140[0m[39m:    private boolean enableSubstitutionInVariables;[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m141[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m142[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95m-----------------------------------------------------------------------[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m143[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m144[0m[39m:     * Creates a new instance with defaults for variable prefix and suffix[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m145[0m[39m:     * and the escaping character.[0m                                              [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m573[0m[39m:     * @param source  the source to replace in, null returns null[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m574[0m[39m:     * @return the result of the replace operation[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m575[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m576[0m[39m:    public String [0m[1;35mreplace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal Object source[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m577[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mreplace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull, source[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m578[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m579[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95m-----------------------------------------------------------------------[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m580[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m581[0m[39m:     * Replaces all the occurrences of variables in the given source object [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwith[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m582[0m[39m:     * their matching values from the resolver. The input source object is[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m583[0m[39m:     * converted to a string using <code>toString<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m> and is not altered.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m584[0m[39m:     *[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m585[0m[39m:     * @param event the current LogEvent, if one exists.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m586[0m[39m:     * @param source  the source to replace in, null returns null[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m587[0m[39m:     * @return the result of the replace operation[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m588[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m589[0m[39m:    public String [0m[1;35mreplace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal LogEvent event, final Object source[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m590[0m[39m:        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msource == null[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m591[0m[39m:            return null;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m592[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m593[0m[39m:        final StringBuilder buf = new [0m[1;35mStringBuilder[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m.append[0m[1;39m([0m[39msource[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m594[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35msubstitute[0m[1;39m([0m[39mevent, buf, [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, [0m[1;35mbuf.length[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m595[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mbuf.toString[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m596[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m597[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m598[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95m-----------------------------------------------------------------------[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m599[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m600[0m[39m:     * Replaces all the occurrences of variables within the given source buffer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcore/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/Interpolator.jav[0m[1;92ma:62[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m68[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m:    public [0m[1;35mInterpolator[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m63[0m[39m:        this.defaultLookup = new [0m[1;35mMapLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnew HashMap<String, String>[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m64[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"sys"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mSystemPropertiesLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m65[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"env"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mEnvironmentLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m66[0m[39m:        [0m[1;35mlookups.put[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"jndi"[0m[39m, new [0m[1;35mJndiLookup[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m67[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m68[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcore/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookup.jav[0m[1;92ma:31[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m36[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m31[0m[39m:    private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m** JNDI resourcce path prefix used in a J2EE container *[0m[35m/[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m:    static final String CONTAINER_JNDI_RESOURCE_PATH_PREFIX = [0m[32m"java:comp/env/"[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Introduce a system‐property toggle and tighten default behavior in JndiLookup:[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookup.java, replace the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munconditional default [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;` with:[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         static [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Default to disabled; users must explicitly opt in[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             ENABLE_JNDI = [0m[1;35mBoolean.parseBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                 [0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"false"[0m[1;39m)[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. At the start of the `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, add:[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m JNDI lookups globally disabled[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             return null;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ```[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Restrict “jndi:” lookups to only local container resources:[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   After extracting the JNDI resource name [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. via regex group[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, insert:[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mresourceName.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCONTAINER_JNDI_RESOURCE_PATH_PREFIX[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Block remote URLs such as ldap:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m, rmi:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m, etc.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mLOGGER.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Remote JNDI lookups are disabled by default: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mresourceName[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return null;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preserve programmatic override:[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep the existing `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` methods.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - With the new static initializer, `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` or [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`-Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndi[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m` will turn on lookups—but still only for [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`jav[0m[1;92ma:c[0m[39momp/env/[0m[33m...[0m[39m` names.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. No changes to Interpolator or StrSubstitutor:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Registration of the “jndi” lookup remains unchanged, but its implementation [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnow enforces the enable‐flag and protocol restrictions.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This approach ensures that message formatting, substitution logic, and all [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mother lookups continue unmodified.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Add regression tests:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that by default `$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mjndi:ldap:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/attacker/[0m[95ma[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` yields `null` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor empty[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatted output.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify that after `[0m[1;35mSystem.setProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m[39m,[0m[32m"true"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.setEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, `$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mjndi:jav[0m[1;92ma:c[0m[39momp/env/jdbc/MyDS[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` still resolves[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas before, but `$[0m[1;39m{[0m[39mjndi:ldap:[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[95m...[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` remains blocked.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Documentation & release notes:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Document the new `log4j2.enableJndi` system property [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefault `false`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moutline how to enable container‐local lookups.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Warn users about the behavior change: code that previously relied on remote [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJNDI must now explicitly opt in.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Disables the high‐risk remote JNDI lookup by default, closing the vulnerability [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwithout altering the fuzzer harness or any external tests.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Allows existing legitimate container‐scoped JNDI usages to continue when [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexplicitly re‐enabled.[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Avoids broad exception swallowing; illegal lookups return `null` and optionally [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlog a warning—preserving existing substitution and formatting flows.[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Mirrors the widely adopted Log4Shell mitigation pattern for system‐property [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontrol and protocol filtering.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1m([0mSimpleLoggerFuzzer.jav[1;92ma:42[0m[1m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         DEDUP_TOKEN: 03a39a742f79fa3d                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         == libFuzzer crashing input ==                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         The fuzzer detected a critical security issue in Log4j’s JndiLookup class:          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         uncontrolled remote JNDI lookups may lead to remote code execution or data          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         exfiltration. To mitigate this, a patch was proposed that disables JNDI lookups by  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         default, introduces a system-property toggle [1m([0m`log4j2.enableJndi`[1m)[0m, adds a new      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mlookup[0m[1m([0mString[1m)[0m` overload enforcing a container-only prefix, and warns on other     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         uses. After applying the patch, the core module failed to compile with multiple     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         “illegal start of expression” and “[32m';'[0m expected” errors in `JndiLookup.java`,       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         indicating mismatched braces, missing method definitions, and overall malformed     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Java syntax.                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A Jazzer fuzzer crash surfaced a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Lookup` exception.                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The stack trace leads into                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup.lookup[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m`, invoked during       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         message formatting [1m([0m`MessagePatternConverter.format`[1m)[0m.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Unrestricted JNDI lookups on attacker-controlled URLs can enable RCE or        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         information leaks depending on the JVM.                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Key Observations from the Initial Issue                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The vulnerability is rooted in Log4j’s default behavior of looking up          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         arbitrary JNDI URLs in log messages.                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The crash input demonstrates how a malformed or malicious lookup key           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         propagates through the `StrSubstitutor` and into `JndiLookup`.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The harness code [1m([0m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer`[1m)[0m triggers a `[1;35mwarn[0m[1m([0m[33m...[0m[1m)[0m` call in the     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         logger, indirectly invoking the insecure lookup logic.                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt Details                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The line initializing `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;` was         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         replaced by a two-step declaration plus a `static` block reading                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m, [32m"false"[0m[1m)[0m`.                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The existing `public String [1;35mlookup[0m[1m([0mLogEvent event, String key[1m)[0m` method was     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         modified to return early if JNDI is disabled.                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A new overload `public String [1;35mlookup[0m[1m([0mString key[1m)[0m` was added, checking          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`, filtering on the `jav[1;92ma:c[0momp/env/` prefix, and issuing a logger    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         warning for disallowed lookups.                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The call to `new [1;35mInitialContext[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` was changed to `final Context ctx = new     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mInitialContext[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`.                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Compilation Log After Patch                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Maven reported [1;36m16[0m compilation errors in `JndiLookup.java`, including:          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • illegal start of expression                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • ‘;’ expected                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • ‘.class’ expected                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • reached end of file while parsing                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Errors clustered around lines [1;36m62[0m, [1;36m86[0m, [1;36m94[0m, [1;36m98[0m and the file end, indicating      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         mismatched or missing braces, missing method declarations [1m([0me.g., no                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m`[1m)[0m, and overlapping method signatures.                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The structure of `JndiLookup.java`: verify class-level and method-level brace  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         balance, ensure each method is correctly opened and closed.                         [2m                [0m
