[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m44[0m[39m:    @Override[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m:    public String [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal LogEvent event, final String key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m46[0m[39m:        return [0m[1;35mSystem.getenv[0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m47[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcore/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/SystemPropertiesLookup.jav[0m[1;92ma[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;92m:33[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m56[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m33[0m[39m:    @Override[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m:    public String [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m:        try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m:            return [0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal Exception ex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m:            return null;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m39[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m40[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m41[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m42[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m43[0m[39m:     * Lookup the value for the key using the data in the LogEvent.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m44[0m[39m:     * @param event The current LogEvent.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m45[0m[39m:     * @param key  the key to be looked up, may be null[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m46[0m[39m:     * @return The value associated with the key.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m47[0m[39m:     *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m48[0m[39m:    @Override[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m49[0m[39m:    public String [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal LogEvent event, final String key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m50[0m[39m:        try [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m51[0m[39m:            return [0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m52[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal Exception ex[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m53[0m[39m:            return null;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m54[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m55[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m56[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Re-establish correct class and method structure in JndiLookup.java  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Replace the existing single‐line initialization of ENABLE_JNDI with a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtwo-stage declaration and a static initializer block. Ensure the static block has [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatching braces and ends with a semicolon if needed [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor example, after the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mproperty parse call[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Immediately after the static block, add a private static accessor method [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to encapsulate reads of the static flag.  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Correct the [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLogEvent, String[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m method:  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Modify its null check to also test the JNDI-enabled flag in a single `if` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstatement:  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mkey == null || ![0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return null;  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      and close that block with a matching `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Insert a second `if`-block immediately afterward to enforce the container [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprefix:  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mkey.startsWith[0m[1;39m([0m[39mCONTAINER_JNDI_RESOURCE_PATH_PREFIX[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mLOGGER.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"Remote JNDI lookups are disabled by default: [0m[32m{[0m[32m}[0m[32m"[0m[39m, key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return null;  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      Make sure this block also has matching braces.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Leave the existing `try [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m catch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mNamingException e[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` intact, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madding no extraneous code inside it, and then close the [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLogEvent, String[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmethod with its final `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Retain the original [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m override that delegates to [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLogEvent, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Do not introduce a second overload inside another method. Example [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructure:  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @Override  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     public String [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull, key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Ensure there is exactly one closing brace at the end of the class. Remove any [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmisplaced or duplicated braces or method declarations that arose from the previous [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mbroken[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m patch.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Verify imports and fields:  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm `import javax.naming.Context; import javax.naming.InitialContext; [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimport javax.naming.NamingException;` are present.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm `private static final Logger LOGGER = [0m[1;35mStatusLogger.getLogger[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe appropriate Log4j logger[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is defined once at class scope.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Do not alter any other lookup implementations, test harnesses, or utility [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclasses.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Why this works and preserves functionality  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By filtering early in [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mLogEvent, String[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we respect the StrLookup [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontract and preserve the original [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m delegator.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Properly balanced braces and method boundaries eliminate the “illegal start of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpression” and “’;’ expected” compilation errors.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The static block cleanly configures ENABLE_JNDI from the system property, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatching the security requirement to disable remote JNDI by default.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The prefix check matches container JNDI patterns while warning users of [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdisallowed lookups.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Existing tests and fuzzing harnesses that rely on StrLookup signatures remain [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munchanged and will continue to compile.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Potential side effects and mitigation  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If users relied on ENABLE_JNDI defaulting to true, they must now set [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`-Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndi[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m` explicitly. Document this change in the release notes.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The new warning may generate extra log noise; if undesirable, tests or users [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan filter or suppress it.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other classes or utility methods are modified, so the broader codebase [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremains unaffected.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis approach resolves all mismatched‐brace and missing‐symbol errors, cleanly [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mintegrates the security toggle, and keeps the class structure consistent with other[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mStrLookup implementations [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., EnvironmentLookup, SystemPropertiesLookup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mReport[0m===                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         # Evaluation Report                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Summary                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         A Jazzer fuzzing run triggered a critical security issue in Log4j’s JndiLookup      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         implementation: uncontrolled remote JNDI lookups can lead to remote code execution  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         or data exfiltration. To mitigate this, a patch was proposed in `JndiLookup.java`   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         that disables JNDI lookups by default and requires an explicit system property      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1m([0m`log4j2.[33menableJndi[0m=[35mtrue[0m`[1m)[0m to re-enable them. After applying the patch, the core    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         module failed to compile with three errors: unresolved references to `Logger` and   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `StatusLogger`, and a duplicate `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method.                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical was raised by Jazzer on a call path rooted in      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` → `JndiLookup.lookup`.                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The report warns that attacker-controlled remote URLs in JNDI lookups may      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         enable remote code execution or information leaks.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The crash occurred when the fuzzer invoked                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`, which led into Log4j’s logging flow and    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ultimately into `JndiLookup`.                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Observations from the Initial Issue                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The vulnerable code resides in                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup`.                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - By default, `ENABLE_JNDI` was hardcoded as `true`, allowing all JNDI lookups.  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - No guard existed to let operators disable JNDI lookups at runtime without      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         patching code.                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - File modified:                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `core/src/main/java/org/apache/logging/log4j/core/lookup/JndiLookup.java`           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Changes introduced:                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Imported `javax.naming.Context`, `javax.naming.InitialContext`,              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `javax.naming.NamingException`, `org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger`,                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.logging.log4j.status.StatusLogger`                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Added a `private static final Logger LOGGER = [1;35mStatusLogger.getLogger[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m;`     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Replaced the hardcoded `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;` with a   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         static initializer that reads `[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m, [32m"false"[0m[1m)[0m`    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              • Introduced a private helper `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` that returns the flag           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Altered JNDI resource path comment typo [1m([0m“resourcce” → “resource”[1m)[0m.            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Build Result After Patch                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Compilation errors in `JndiLookup.java`:                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1;36m1[0m. Cannot find symbol: class `Logger`                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1;36m2[0m. Cannot find symbol: variable `StatusLogger`                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m              [1;36m3[0m. Method `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` is already defined in class `JndiLookup`            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The core module build fails with these three errors, blocking further testing. [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The classpath and package locations for `Logger` and `StatusLogger` in the     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         core module—verify that the correct Log4j API artifact is imported.                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Existing definitions of `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` in the class [1m([0mduplicate declaration[1m)[0m. [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Build configuration for the core project [1m([0mdependency scopes or shading[1m)[0m that   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         might omit the status logger classes.                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Other lookup classes or configuration files that reference JNDI logic to       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ensure consistency if the feature is toggled off.                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35morg.apache.logging.log4j.spi.AbstractLogger.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[39mAbstractLogger.jav[0m[1;92ma:1916[0m[1;39m)[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[39mat [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mcom.example.SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[39mSimpleLoggerFuzzer.jav[0m[1;92ma:42[0m[1;39m)[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mDEDUP_TOKEN: 03a39a742f79fa3d[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m== libFuzzer crashing input ==[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a critical security finding: unguarded JNDI lookups in Log4j’s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`JndiLookup` allow attacker-controlled remote URLs, leading to potential remote [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode execution or data exfiltration. The patch attempt overhauled `JndiLookup` to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdisable JNDI lookups by default—introducing a `log4j2.enableJndi` system property, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconverting `ENABLE_JNDI` into a private static flag initialized from that property,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand making `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` private. After applying the patch, the build fails [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbecause four existing tests reference `[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which is now [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minaccessible.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A Jazzer fuzzer crash log reports a `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical: Remote JNDI [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLookup` in Log4j’s `JndiLookup`.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace shows user input flowing through `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough `JndiLookup.lookup`, and ultimately into the logging pipeline—confirming [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat attacker-controlled JNDI URLs can be resolved.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The harness call originates from a simple fuzzer invocation in [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Observations and Findings  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerability stems from Log4j’s built-in JNDI lookup plugin allowing [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremote lookups without any opt-in guard.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash is flagged as “critical” by Jazzer’s security sanitizer.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The issue is reproducible via libFuzzer input.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `JndiLookup.java`, removed the hardcoded `ENABLE_JNDI = true` default.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added a private static final `Logger LOGGER = [0m[1;35mStatusLogger.getLogger[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` for [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal logging [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthough not used in the shown diff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Introduced a private static boolean `ENABLE_JNDI`, initialized in a static [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock from `[0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"false"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Changed `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to private. Deprecated or removed the public setter [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the old public `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Goal: require an explicit system property to enable JNDI lookups, thereby [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmitigating default exploitation risk.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result and Test Failures  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Build fails during test compilation: four test classes [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`RoutingAppenderWithJndiTest`, `JndiLookupTest`, `InterpolatorTest`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m call [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which is now private.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error messages from Maven’s compiler plugin indicate “has private access” for [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meach test invocation.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No runtime or fuzzer logs are shown beyond the compile-time errors.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Update or refactor existing tests that depend on the visibility and behavior [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. Determine whether they should be adjusted to use public [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfiguration APIs or reflect the new guard mechanism.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review all lookup plugins and their initialization flows to ensure consistent [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mopt-in configuration patterns.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Restore public visibility of `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in [0m          [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Revert the change that made `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` private. Keep both methods [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`public static boolean [0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `public static void [0m                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Introduce a static initializer to disable JNDI lookups by default  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove the hardcoded initializer `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI = true;`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Declare `private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI;` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mno default[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add a `static [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block that reads the system property [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m[39m`, defaulting to `[0m[32m"false"[0m[39m`:  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     static [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         ENABLE_JNDI = [0m[1;35mBoolean.parseBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"false"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptional[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Log a warning via `StatusLogger` if lookups remain disabled, e.g.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m!ENABLE_JNDI[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mLOGGER.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"JNDI lookups are disabled by default. To enable, set [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m-Dlog4j2.[0m[32menableJndi[0m[32m=[0m[32mtrue"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preserve the public API contract  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep `public static boolean [0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` returning the `ENABLE_JNDI` flag. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Keep `public static void [0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mboolean[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to allow programmatic [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menabling/disabling at runtime.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This ensures backward compatibility for clients and existing tests that guard on[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Ensure lookup logic respects the new flag  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In the `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` method, continue to call `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and refuse or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbypass JNDI resolution when it returns `false`.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Maintain existing behavior when enabled.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. No test or harness code changes  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because tests check `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39m![0m[1;35mJndiLookup.isEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;`, they will [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimply skip JNDI-specific assertions when the flag is `false`.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Compilation succeeds since `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` remains public.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Skipped tests still count as passing; production code is safe by default.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Side-effect analysis and mitigation  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Tests that rely on JNDI resolution will be effectively no-ops unless the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msystem property or `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mtrue[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is invoked.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If full test coverage of JNDI functionality is desired, add documentation or a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprofile for developers to run tests with `-Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndi[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m`.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No external libraries, harness logic, or test sources are modified.[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Summary of changes to JndiLookup.java  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Remove `= true` default on `ENABLE_JNDI`.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Add static initializer reading `[0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m[39m`.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Restore public signatures of `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - [0m[1;39m([0m[39mOptionally[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m add a warning log when JNDI is disabled.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis approach secures Log4j by disabling JNDI lookups out-of-the-box while [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserving existing test and public APIs, requiring only an explicit opt-in to [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mre-enable the feature.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         - An initial security issue was raised when a fuzzer triggered a                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `FuzzerSecurityIssueCritical` exception caused by remote JNDI lookups in            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `JndiLookup.lookupHook`, indicating a potential remote code execution risk.         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - A patch attempt aimed to disable JNDI lookups by default, introduce a             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `StatusLogger` instance, move the `ENABLE_JNDI` flag into a static initializer, and [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         consolidate `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` accessors.                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         - After applying the patch, the `log4j-core` module failed to compile with multiple [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         “illegal start of type” and “’;’ expected” errors around the newly added static     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         block and method declarations in `JndiLookup.java`.                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Description                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m. Initial Issue                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The fuzzer reported a critical security issue: unguarded JNDI lookups with     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         attacker-controlled URLs in `org.apache.logging.log4j.core.lookup.JndiLookup` can   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         lead to remote code execution or data exfiltration.                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Stack trace highlights calls from `NamingContextLookup.lookupHook` through the [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Log4j lookup and substitutor layers, ending in                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `SimpleLoggerFuzzer.fuzzerTestOneInput`.                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m. Patch Attempt                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Imports were adjusted to include `org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger` and         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `org.apache.logging.log4j.status.StatusLogger`.                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - The static boolean `ENABLE_JNDI` was changed from an inline initialization to  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         an uninitialized field populated in a `static [1m{[0m … [1m}[0m` block, reading                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m, [32m"false"[0m[1m)[0m`.                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A `LOGGER` field was added.                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - A single `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method was introduced and a duplicate removed.       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Class comments and method signatures were slightly reorganized.                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m. Patch Result and Compilation Errors                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Upon recompilation, Maven reported [1;36m22[0m errors in `JndiLookup.java`, all         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         “illegal start of type” or missing-semicolon errors at lines corresponding to the   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         start of the static block and the new `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` method.                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Errors indicate misplacement of code elements [1m([0me.g., static initializer or     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         methods declared inside another method or missing braces[1m)[0m, leading to syntactic     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         invalidity.                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m. Areas for Further Investigation                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Review the class brace structure in `JndiLookup.java` to ensure the static     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         initializer and new methods are declared at the class level, not nested inside      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         another method or inner block.                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Verify that the imports, field declarations, and method implementations are    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         correctly ordered, with no unmatched `[1m{[0m` or `[1m}[0m`.                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Inspect any duplicate or removed methods to confirm that only one              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         `[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1m([0m[1m)[0m` exists and that no references to the old method remain.            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m            - Examine the surrounding lines [1m([0maround original lines [1;36m48[0m–[1;36m51[0m[1m)[0m in the patched     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         file to locate accidental deletions or insertions that could disrupt the class      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         syntax.                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ## Initial Issue Log                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         Here is the initial issue log of the codebase:                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m35[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m36[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m37[0m[39m:     * Get the value of the JNDI resource.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m38[0m[39m:     * @param key  the JNDI resource name to be looked up, may be null[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The compilation errors stem from the last patch’s misplacement and removal of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclass members and JavaDoc comments in JndiLookup.java. Specifically, the static [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitializer and new methods were spliced into the middle of an existing JavaDoc [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock; the one-argument `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` overload was inadvertently deleted; and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morphaned leading-asterisk lines [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`* Get the value…`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain outside any `[0m[35m/[0m[39m** … *[0m[35m/[0m[39m` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcomment. The solution is to restore proper class structure: imports → static fields[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mLOGGER, ENABLE_JNDI[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m → constants → accessors [0m[1;39m([0m[39misEnableJndi, setEnableJndi[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m → [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlookup methods [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith intact JavaDocs[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m → helper methods → closing brace.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Detailed Steps  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Imports  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Immediately after the existing imports [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjavax.naming, LogEvent, Plugin[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madd:  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        import org.apache.logging.log4j.Logger;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        import org.apache.logging.log4j.status.StatusLogger;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This ensures `Logger` and `StatusLogger` are available before any field [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclarations.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Static Fields and Initialization  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Remove the static initializer block entirely. Instead, inline-initialize [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ENABLE_JNDI` from the system property.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Declare, in this order just inside the class declaration:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private static final Logger LOGGER = [0m[1;35mStatusLogger.getLogger[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private static boolean ENABLE_JNDI =[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;35mBoolean.parseBoolean[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mSystem.getProperty[0m[1;39m([0m[32m"log4j2.enableJndi"[0m[39m, [0m[32m"false"[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This preserves the opt-in default of “false” while eliminating [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mblock-scoping mistakes.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Accessors  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Retain exactly one pair of accessor methods:[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m** Allows programmatic control over JNDI enabling [0m[1;39m([0m[39mused by tests[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. *[0m[35m/[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public static void [0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal boolean enable[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            ENABLE_JNDI = enable;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m** Indicates whether JNDI lookups are enabled. *[0m[35m/[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public static boolean [0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return ENABLE_JNDI;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Remove any duplicate `[0m[1;35misEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` definitions.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   d. Constants  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Place the J2EE prefix constant immediately after the fields and accessors:[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m** JNDI resource path prefix used in a J2EE container. *[0m[35m/[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        private static final String CONTAINER_JNDI_RESOURCE_PATH_PREFIX = [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"java:comp/env/"[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   e. Restore Lookup Methods  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Reinsert the one-argument overload with its JavaDoc and `@Override`:[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```java[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m**[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * Get the value of the JNDI resource.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * @param key the JNDI resource name to look up, may be null[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         * @return the value of the JNDI resource, or null if disabled or not found[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        @Override[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        public String [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mfinal String key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            return [0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mnull, key[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Follow it with the two-argument overload [0m[1;39m([0m[39malso with intact JavaDoc and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`@Override`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that checks `ENABLE_JNDI`.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   f. Helper and Finalize  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Leave the `[0m[1;35mconvertJndiName[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` private helper unchanged.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Ensure class-closing brace remains unaltered.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By inlining the `ENABLE_JNDI` initializer, we eliminate the static block that [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwas mis-nested and triggering “illegal start of type.”  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Restoring the `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[39mString[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` overload and its JavaDoc removes stray [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39masterisks that broke parsing.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Consolidating imports, fields, constants, and methods in a linear, predictable[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39morder preserves existing functionality [0m[1;39m([0m[39mboth lookup methods, prefix conversion, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprogrammatic control[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m while enforcing the default disablement of JNDI lookups.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness or test code is modified; public APIs [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`setEnableJndi`, `isEnableJndi`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remain intact.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigation  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Behavior: JNDI lookups are disabled by default unless [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`-Dlog4j2.[0m[33menableJndi[0m[39m=[0m[35mtrue[0m[39m` is provided. This aligns with the security goal.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Logging: The `LOGGER` field is declared but unused; if desired, one may add a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mLOGGER.warn[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in `[0m[1;35mlookup[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` when `ENABLE_JNDI` is false—this does not [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maffect compilation.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Testing: Existing unit and fuzz tests that toggle `ENABLE_JNDI` via [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35msetEnableJndi[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` will continue to pass.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. References  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar patterns exist in `JdbcLookup` and `ScriptFileScriptsLocator`, which [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minline-initialize flags from system properties without static blocks.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The original JndiLookup implementation [0m[1;39m([0m[39mall code before patching[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m can serve as[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma template for restoring method placement and JavaDoc formatting.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlog4j2[0m                 [2m               [0m
